<subSubSection id="3BE66555D5715D04CE86FBACFE954D5C" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="734336DED5715D04CE86FBACFE954D5C" blockId="32.[192,1440,1057,1370]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CE86FBACFED74C3F" bold="true" box="[192,349,1057,1081]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CF21FBAFFDCC4C3F" box="[359,582,1058,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aztecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CF21FBAFFDCC4C3F" box="[359,582,1058,1082]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Purenleon aztecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CCB6FBAFFCFA4C3C" box="[752,880,1058,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toltecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CCB6FBAFFCFA4C3C" box="[752,880,1058,1082]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. toltecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CDF7FBAFFBA04C3C" authorityName="Miller and Stange Ventral" authorityYear="2014" box="[945,1066,1058,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apache">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CDF7FBAFFBA04C3C" box="[945,1066,1058,1082]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. apache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the forefemur with numerous long setae on exterior face and the forecoxa has numerous elongate setae on lateral face in addition to elongate white setae on posterior margin 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CD37FBEFFC614C7F" box="[881,1003,1122,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aztecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CD37FBEFFC614C7F" box="[881,1003,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. aztecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from both 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CA8CFBEFFAC34C7C" box="[1226,1353,1122,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toltecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CA8CFBEFFAC34C7C" box="[1226,1353,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. toltecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CBC1FBEFFE9C4C9C" authorityName="Miller and Stange Ventral" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apache">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CBC1FBEFFE9C4C9C" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. apache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the hind margin of forewing from near base to well beyond midpoint of wing dark brown suffused (
<figureCitation id="EBC72A5BD5715D04CFC8FB2FFE6E4CBF" box="[398,484,1185,1210]" captionStart="Figures 58–62" captionStartId="31.[192,288,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,870,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-324@31.[192,1440,870,1848]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figures 58–62. Purenleon aztecus Miller and Stange, adult. 58) head and thorax; 59) lateral view; 60) wings; 61) male genitalia; 62) female terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5179554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5179554/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) and the tibial spurs of hindleg reach only a little beyond apex of basitarsus; also the thoracic pleura of 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CC46FB4FFDF34CDF" box="[512,633,1218,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aztecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CC46FB4FFDF34CDF" box="[512,633,1218,1241]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. aztecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CCF5FB4FFCBA4CDC" box="[691,816,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toltecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CCF5FB4FFCBA4CDC" box="[691,816,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. toltecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have numerous, distally swollen white setae which is diagnostic in the group The larva agrees with 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CD40FB6FFCF14CFC" authorityName="Miller and Stange Ventral" authorityYear="2014" box="[774,891,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apache">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CD40FB6FFCF14CFC" box="[774,891,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. apache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D5DD5715D04CDF3FB6FFBB84CFC" box="[949,1074,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toltecus">
<emphasis id="4188EACCD5715D04CDF3FB6FFBB84CFC" box="[949,1074,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. toltecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having having a prominent sublateral row of dolichasters posterior to the lateral tentorial suture on the dorsal head capsule. Also, the abdominal spiracles are easily visible, although shorter than or equal to basal width in these three species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
